gomodel:SYNGO_5060  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figure 1: expression of IgSF11 increases during rat brain development, is enriched in PSD biochemical fractions, interacts with PSD-95 (DLG4) in HEK293T cells and in vivo, co-localizes with PSD-95 at dendritic spines of cultured rat hippocampal neurons.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein (Figure 1a), \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"(j) IgSF11 is targeted dendritic spines in a PDZ binding-dependent manner. In cultured rat hippocampal neurons transfected with PSD-95 + IgSF11 WT/ΔC3 (DIV14-17)\"\n\nantibody:\n\"MBP fusion proteins containing human IgSF11 (aa 262-430) were used for immunization of guinea pigs (2003), and peptides containing mouse IgSF11 (aa 399-427) were used to immunize guinea pigs (2067) and rabbits (2068 and 2070). The specificity of anti-IgSF11 antibodies (2003) was confirmed by immunoblot experiments using Igsf11-/- brain lysates.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5060" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

